### Manual smoke tests — run from VS Code (REST Client) or Rider. Docs UI: {{host}}/scalar
### Identity comes from an external provider (Google/GitHub); in Development you can also use
### /auth/dev-login (email only, no password).
@host = http://localhost:5170

### health
GET {{host}}/health

### which providers are wired up (+ whether dev-login is available)
GET {{host}}/auth/providers

### dev login (Development only) — sets the session cookie
POST {{host}}/auth/dev-login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "test@example.com", "displayName": "Tester" }

### who am I
GET {{host}}/auth/me

### start the real OAuth flow (opens the provider) — visit in a browser
GET {{host}}/auth/login/google?returnUrl=http://localhost:3000

### my signed-in devices
GET {{host}}/auth/sessions

### logout (revokes this device's session)
POST {{host}}/auth/logout
